-------------
Prerequisites
-------------

 - Java 8
 - Maven 3.0.5 or higher
 - Node.js 0.12 (http://nodejs.org)
 - Grunt (http://gruntjs.org)
 - Bower (http://bower.io)
 - Git (http://git-scm.org) - needed by Bower

Grunt and Bower can be installed with Node Package Manager (provided and installed with Node.js):

 $ sudo npm install -g grunt-cli bower

-----------------------------
Linux-specific instructions
-----------------------------

For installing Node.js 0.12 on Linux via package manager, see:

  https://github.com/joyent/node/wiki/Installing-Node.js-via-package-manager

or (as currently linked to):

  https://nodesource.com/blog/nodejs-v012-iojs-and-the-nodesource-linux-repositories

  Note for Linux Mint users:
    The referenced script from the above blog post might fail trying to uninstall the ppa:chris-lea/node.js repository!
    See also: https://bugs.launchpad.net/linuxmint/+bug/1341617
    In that case, first manually remove that repository configuration like this:

       $ sudo rm /etc/apt/sources.list.d/chris-lea-node_js-*.list

-----------------------------
Windows-specific instructions
-----------------------------

You can automate the installation of Node.js using Chocolatey package manager:

    https://chocolatey.org/

The package for Node.js can be installed using:

  $ cinst nodejs.install

Then install Bower and Grunt with NPM as explained before.

-----
Build
-----

Build with testing:

 $ mvn clean install

Build without testing:

 $ mvn clean install -DskipTests

Build with snapshot dependencies:

 $ mvn clean install -Dhippo.snapshots=true

 Note: only needed when the project refers to SNAPSHOT dependencies!

 Note: only effective when your Maven settings.xml file contains a profile
       with this property for the Hippo snapshot repository. For details, see
       http://www.onehippo.org/library/development/build-hippo-cms-from-scratch.html
